26 incumbent electricity supplier.
27 (2) As a condition of receiving and maintaining a license, a
28 competitive electricity supplier must do the following:
29 (A) Pay to the commission an annual licensing fee of ten
30 thousand dollars ($10,000).
31 (B) Execute and maintain a surety bond, or an equivalent
32 financial security instrument, that is:
33 (i) issued by a qualified surety, insurance company, or
34 other financial institution authorized to do business in
35 Indiana;
36 (ii) in the amount of not less than one million dollars
37 ($1,000,000); and
38 (iii) paid by the competitive electricity supplier.
39 In submitting an application for a license to the
40 commission, the competitive electricity supplier shall
41 include a copy of the required surety bond or financial
42 security instrument, including a notarized verification
